snippet.title: Diamond Platnumz feat Bien - Katam (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Get Katam👇👇👇
https://dplatnumz.lnk.to/katam

"KATAM" is a sweet, catchy love anthem that brings together two East African powerhouses—Diamond Platnumz and @BienOfficial in a celebration of beauty, love, and unity across the continent. The song produced by S2Kizzy is all about that one special woman who leaves you completely speechless—her vibe, her shape, her roots—everything about her is katam tam, meaning irresistibly sweet. Through playful lyrics and smooth harmonies, Diamond and Bien paint a picture of a woman whose charm reflects the richness of East Africa—from her Rwandan glow, Somali hair, Ethiopian eyes, to her Tanzanian sweetness and Kenyan smarts. It's flirty, fun, and full of pride—an Afro-pop jam that makes you want to dance, fall in love, and raise a toast to all the beautiful queens of Africa."

snippet.title: Mbosso - Pawa (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by Mbosso performing, “Pawa” (Power), is a heartfelt, poetic love song by Mbosso that captures the overwhelming power of deep affection. Using rich metaphors and smooth vocals, he likens love to an intoxicating force that leaves him weak and emotionally charged — “naishiwa pawa” (I’m losing power). The lyrics blend vulnerability with admiration, painting his lover as a source of strength and inspiration. With a melodic blend of Bongo Flava and soulful instrumentation, “Pawa” showcases Mbosso’s lyrical depth and emotive style. The music was shot in Iringa, Tanzania, Directed by Folex & Audio produced by S2Kizzy.

snippet.title: The Next Generation of Heroes? 😂 | Superpower Tryouts at Zoom Academy! #movie #shorts #edit
snippet.description: Step into one of the most hilarious and heartwarming scenes from Zoom: Academy for Superheroes, where kids from across the country show up to audition for the ultimate honor—becoming the next generation of superheroes! 💥From invisibility mishaps to super strength that’s just a bit too strong, this tryout session is anything but ordinary. Led by the reluctant hero Captain Zoom, the team searches for young recruits who might save the world—or at least survive training camp! 😄Watch as each kid reveals their quirky and sometimes unpredictable powers. Some impress, some cause a few laughs (and minor explosions), but all of them have something special. It's a chaotic mix of chaos, comedy, and surprising moments of heart. ❤️Whether you're here for the action, the laughs, or the nostalgia of early 2000s superhero films, this scene is a must-watch. snippet.title: Kenya Protest LIVE: Police Block Roads To Nairobi on Anniversary of Pro-Democracy Protests | N18G
snippet.description:
Kenya Protest LIVE: Protests in Nairobi, Kenya on Anniversary of Historic Pro-Democracy March | CNBC TV18
Nairobi, Kenya - Protests expected in Kenya on anniversary of historic pro-democracy march. Known as Saba Saba (Seven Seven), July 7 is remembered as the day Kenyans took to the streets in 1990 demanding multi-party democracy. This year, the anniversary is set against a backdrop of rising public anger over police brutality, abductions of activists, corruption, and a deepening economic crisis. Protesters are expected to gather in the Central Business District, with a strong police presence anticipated.
Kenyans hold a protest in Nairobi against police brutality, as anger has reignited over the longstanding issue by the death of blogger Albert Ojwang in police custody and the close-range shooting by police of vendor Boniface Kariuki during protests for Ojwang mid-June. Human rights groups have long called for action over illegal arrests, detentions and torture of government critics in Kenya. President William Ruto has vowed to end police brutality and said no enforced disappearances would happen during his administration. But Ruto's interior minister told police to “shoot on sight” anyone who approaches police stations during protests, after five police stations were torched.
#kenyanews #sabasaba #nairobi #kenyanpolitics #livenews #cnbctv18

snippet.title: Kenya descends into CHAOS as MASSIVE violent protests erupt against police brutality
snippet.description:
Thousands of protesters took to the streets in Nairobi on Wednesday, clashing with police over issues of police brutality and government corruption, as demonstrations spread nationwide.

The confrontations saw police deploying tear gas and using batons, resulting in several injuries. These protests coincide with the one-year anniversary of anti-tax demonstrations that led to 60 deaths and left 20 individuals missing.

The unrest has now extended to major cities such as Mombasa, Kisumu, Nakuru, and Nyahururu, evolving into demands for the president's resignation over allegations of poor governance.

Kenyan youth are particularly dissatisfied with the current administration, citing corruption, a rising cost of living, and police brutality, further fuelled by the recent death of a blogger in custody.

Public anger has been intensified by the close-range shooting of a civilian during recent demonstrations.

snippet.title: Mbosso - Pawa (Official Lyric Video)
snippet.description:
Track No.1“Pawa” (Power)  is a heartfelt, poetic love song by Mbosso that captures the overwhelming power of deep affection. Using rich metaphors and smooth vocals, he likens love to an intoxicating force that leaves him weak and emotionally charged — “naishiwa pawa” (I’m losing power). The lyrics blend vulnerability with admiration, painting his lover as a source of strength and inspiration. With a melodic blend of Bongo Flava and soulful instrumentation, “Pawa” showcases Mbosso’s lyrical depth and emotive style.
